{{Wikidatabox}} [[File:Katsurarikyu01.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Garden of Katsura Imperial Villa]]
'''Kaiyū-shiki Teien''' (回遊式庭園) is a style of {{ill|Japanese garden|ja|日本庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} designed for strolling and viewing various landscapes within the garden. While strolling-style gardens exist outside Japan, the term "kaiyū-shiki teien" typically refers to Japanese gardens specifically.
== Overview ==
Kaiyū-shiki teien became prominent during the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Zen Buddhism|ja|禅宗|qq=draft|qq=draft}} temples and were extensively developed by {{ill|daimyō|ja|大名|qq=draft|qq=draft}} during the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. This style is considered a culmination of Japanese garden design.
The most common type is the '''{{ill|Pond Strolling Garden|ja|池泉庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}}''' (池泉回遊式庭園), which features a central pond surrounded by paths. These paths allow visitors to enjoy views of {{ill|artificial hills|ja|築山|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, small islands in the pond, bridges, and {{ill|ornamental stones|ja|庭石|qq=draft|qq=draft}} representing scenic locations. Along the pathways, structures such as {{ill|teahouses|ja|茶室|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|azumaya|ja|四阿|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were built to serve as rest stops and observation points.
== Representative Kaiyū-shiki Teien ==
* {{ill|Koishikawa Kōrakuen|ja|小石川後楽園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Bunkyō, Tokyo|ja|文京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - {{ill|Special Historic Site|ja|特別史跡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Special Place of Scenic Beauty|ja|特別名勝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * [[Rikugi-en Gardens]] (Bunkyō, Tokyo) - Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Hama-rikyū Gardens|ja|浜離宮恩賜庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Chūō, Tokyo|ja|中央区 (東京都)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Tokyo) - Special Historic Site and Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Kenroku-en|ja|兼六園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Kanazawa|ja|金沢市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Ishikawa Prefecture|ja|石川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Place of Scenic Beauty * [[:en:Ichijōdani_Asakura_Family_Historic_Ruins|Ichijōdani Asakura Family Historic Ruins]] ({{ill|Fukui|ja|福井市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukui Prefecture|ja|福井県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Historic Site and Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Genkyū-en|ja|玄宮園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Hikone|ja|彦根市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Historic Site and Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Katsura Imperial Villa|ja|桂離宮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden ({{ill|Nishikyō-ku, Kyoto|ja|西京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Kinkaku-ji|ja|鹿苑寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden ({{ill|Kita-ku, Kyoto|ja|北区 (京都市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kyoto) - Special Historic Site, Special Place of Scenic Beauty, and World Heritage Site * {{ill|Ginkaku-ji|ja|慈照寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden ({{ill|Sakyō-ku, Kyoto|ja|左京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kyoto) - Special Historic Site, Special Place of Scenic Beauty, and World Heritage Site * {{ill|Tenryū-ji|ja|天龍寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden ({{ill|Ukyō-ku, Kyoto|ja|右京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kyoto) - Historic Site, Special Place of Scenic Beauty, and World Heritage Site * {{ill|Saihō-ji (Kyoto)|ja|西芳寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden (Nishikyō-ku, Kyoto) - Historic Site, Special Place of Scenic Beauty, and World Heritage Site * {{ill|Nijō Castle|ja|二条城|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Ninomaru Garden ({{ill|Nakagyō-ku, Kyoto|ja|中京区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kyoto) - Historic Site, Special Place of Scenic Beauty, and World Heritage Site * {{ill|Sambō-in Garden|ja|三宝院庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} at {{ill|Daigo-ji|ja|醍醐寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Fushimi-ku, Kyoto|ja|伏見区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kyoto) - Special Historic Site and Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Adachi Museum of Art|ja|足立美術館|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Garden ({{ill|Yasugi|ja|安来市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shimane Prefecture|ja|島根県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Ranked first in a Japanese garden Ranking by the Journal of Japanese Gardening * [[Kōraku-en]] ({{ill|Kita-ku, Okayama|ja|北区 (岡山市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okayama|ja|岡山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okayama Prefecture|ja|岡山県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Ritsurin Garden|ja|栗林公園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Takamatsu|ja|高松市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kagawa Prefecture|ja|香川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Place of Scenic Beauty * {{ill|Shikina-en|ja|識名園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Naha|ja|那覇市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Okinawa Prefecture|ja|沖縄県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) - Special Place of Scenic Beauty and World Heritage Site == See Also == * {{ill|Daimyō garden|ja|大名庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Pond Strolling Garden|ja|池泉庭園|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
